basics.name: Juliette Raubolt
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am studying for a B.S. in Computer Science with a Security Science focus in the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii. I expect to graduate with my bachelor's in Spring, 2024.

work.summary: Conduct programming classes that introduce middle schoolers to coding.
highlights: Each week go to a middle school such as Kaimuki Middle School and conduct introductory lessons on python coding.
Guide students in projects to help them establish programming basics.
Research and experiment with wifi security such as different protocols.
Use tools such as wireshark and aircrack then automate processes with python scripts using scapy.

work.summary: Work alongside various teams in the cybersecurity department.
highlights: Work with the Red Team, Third Party Risk Management and Exceptions Team, and the Compliance Team.
Complete projects and day to day tasks, shadow meetings, and attend webinars.

work.position: Physical Sciences Computer Support Group (PSCSG) student intern
work.summary: Aid in various IT tasks within the Physical Sciences Department.
highlights: Serve as a student intern for the Physical Sciences Computer Support Group.
Assist in any IT tasks for the physical sciences department from web developmentto wifi troubleshooting or network security.

work.summary: Tutor students in math, physics, and computer science.
highlights: Meet with students (mainly high school) for tutoring in various subjects including math, physics, chemistry, and computer science.
Manage communication and scheduling with the students and parents, utilized Calendly for scheduling.

volunteer.summary: Compete in the National Cyber League Capture the Flag competitions with the individual and team game.
Complete as many of the nine tasks released each year in the NSA Codebreakers challenge.
Secure various systems such as Ubuntu machines or Windows servers to the highest degree possible in the alotted four hour time frame.

awards.title: Most Distinguished College Project
awards.summary: Served as the lead for Saddleback's Phi Theta Kappa College Project, a service project meant to serve the college administration. For our project we created a series of tour videos for the campus. We received Most Distinguished College Project for the Nevadea California region and on a national level were recongnized as a Distinguished Chapter Project.
